### **Scientific Impact**

```{r datascholar_load, echo=FALSE, message=FALSE, warning=FALSE}
load("data_scholar.Rdata")
```

The data was automatically retrieved from Google Scholar on the `r data_scholar[["date"]]`.


```{r impactplot, echo=FALSE, message=FALSE, warning=FALSE, out.width = "100%"}
knitr::include_graphics("img/plot_impact.png")
```
<center><sup>*Cumulative citations and publication number, automatically scrapped from Google Scholar.*</sup></center>

```{r citationplot, echo=FALSE, message=FALSE, warning=FALSE, out.width = "100%"}
knitr::include_graphics("img/plot_citations.png")
```
<center><sup>*Sometimes, the total number of citations is strongly driven by few particularly well-cited publications. This plot, showing the number of citations per publication, suggests that most of my papers are rather homogeneously cited.*</sup></center>


<br>

```{r impacttable, echo=FALSE, message=FALSE, warning=FALSE}
data <- data_scholar$scholar_data

knitr::kable(data.frame(
  Metric = c("Total number of publications", 
             "Total number of citations", 
             "Average number of publications / Year", 
             "Average number of citations / Year", 
             # "i10-index"),
             "h-index"),
  Number = c(max(data[data$Index=="Publications", ]$Number), 
            data_scholar$scholar_stats$total_cites,
            round(max(data[data$Index=="Publications", ]$Number) / (max(data$Year) - min(data$Year))),
            round(data_scholar$scholar_stats$total_cites / (max(data$Year) - min(data$Year))),
            # data_scholar$scholar_stats$i10_index,
            data_scholar$scholar_stats$h_index)
))
```


<br>

### **Collaboration Network**

The data is retrieved from the Google Scholar co-author list (that one must update ***manually*** on its scholar profile by clicking the `+` button and accept the suggestions), thus not 100% accurate (e.g., co-authors without a scholar profile are not listed).


```{r network, echo=FALSE, message=FALSE, warning=FALSE, fig.height=10*2, fig.width=10, fig.align='center', include=TRUE, out.width = "100%"}
knitr::include_graphics("img/plot_network.png")
```
<center><sup>*My coauthors network, based on Google Scholar data.*</sup></center>

